### Plan for Launching a Network State Based on Unified Blockchain Technology

1. Develop a standardized blockchain framework designed to integrate multiple existing networks into one platform, ensuring near-infinite scalability and substantial performance enhancement in the short term. This robust foundation will facilitate seamless transfer and operation of digital services globally while maintaining exceptional computational efficiency. (A deeper exploration of infinite scalability challenges appears in Chapter 9. of CIL Omnichain)

2. Implement a decentralized governance system for this consolidated blockchain network referred to as the "Network State" or "Omninet Union." It comprises several committees formed through distinct approaches yet centered around a shared objective—governing planet Earth's resources utilizing smart contracts and Omninet technology. Contrasting conventional blockchains issuing tradable tokens subjected to centralized market forces, the Omninet Union functions independently, empowering expansion not only over blockchain ecosystems but also across broader political landscapes. (Reference CIL 42 Gov)

3. Following the establishment of the Omninet Union, introduce a consistent tax regime throughout all connected blockchains without compromising user privacy. Encourage committee competitiveness to optimize fiscal policies and incentivize tax payment with enticing service offers. Foster cooperation alongside competition, leveraging voluntary participation instead of forceful imposition, thereby fostering a peaceful environment based on mutual benefit rather than conflict. Ultimately, successful implementations exhibiting maximum effectiveness at tax collection shall serve as evidence of delivering premium services and core values worthy of broad adoption.

4. Engage in diplomatic relations with sovereign nations, encouraging their integration into our innovative system. By doing so, we aim to establish harmonious relationships benefitting both local populations and international Network State constituents. Explore prospective agreements incorporating equitable tax distribution mechanisms derived from revenues generated by individuals tied geographically or otherwise to particular countries. Offer opportunities for acquiring "virtual residency" status or Network State citizenship, effectively liberating eligible individuals from burdensome double-taxation obligations imposed by other governments.

5. Collaboratively design bespoke tax allocation schemes catering explicitly to each partnering nation's unique needs. Establish specialized subcommittees comprised of representatives selected using assorted election processes, potentially echoing those employed at the principal level within the Omninet Union hierarchy. Such strategic alignments would promote synergistic interactions between member states and the evolving Network State structure, ultimately cultivating sustainable global development rooted in unity, security, and prosperity.

